The briefing by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and Obama National Security Speechwriter Ben Rhodes took place on September 23, 2009, at the Waldorf Astoria in New York. The briefing covered various topics, including President Obama's speech at the United Nations, the upcoming talks on Iran, the situation in Afghanistan, and the US relationship with Libya. The President emphasized the need for collective action and international cooperation to address global challenges, such as climate change, nuclear proliferation, and the global economic downturn. He also called for an end to political games and urged world leaders to work together to meet these challenges.